set_exponent(x, i) returns a real with fraction(x) and exponent i.
It is like fraction(x) * radix(x)**i.

default real examples:
x = -3.5
  fraction(x)        = -0.875
  exponent(x)        = 2
  set_exponent(x, 0) = -0.875
  set_exponent(x, 1) = -1.75
  set_exponent(x, 2) = -3.5
x = -1
  fraction(x)        = -0.5
  exponent(x)        = 1
  set_exponent(x, 0) = -0.5
  set_exponent(x, 1) = -1
  set_exponent(x, 2) = -2
x = -0.5
  fraction(x)        = -0.5
  exponent(x)        = 0
  set_exponent(x, 0) = -0.5
  set_exponent(x, 1) = -1
  set_exponent(x, 2) = -2
x = 0
  fraction(x)        = 0
  exponent(x)        = 0
  set_exponent(x, 0) = 0
  set_exponent(x, 1) = 0
  set_exponent(x, 2) = 0
x = 0.5
  fraction(x)        = 0.5
  exponent(x)        = 0
  set_exponent(x, 0) = 0.5
  set_exponent(x, 1) = 1
  set_exponent(x, 2) = 2
x = 1
  fraction(x)        = 0.5
  exponent(x)        = 1
  set_exponent(x, 0) = 0.5
  set_exponent(x, 1) = 1
  set_exponent(x, 2) = 2
x = 3.5
  fraction(x)        = 0.875
  exponent(x)        = 2
  set_exponent(x, 0) = 0.875
  set_exponent(x, 1) = 1.75
  set_exponent(x, 2) = 3.5

kind examples:
set_exponent(1.5,   3) = 6
set_exponent(1.5_4, 3) = 6
set_exponent(1.5_8, 3) = 6
